Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.97,0:00:11.26,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.44,0:00:26.35,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Even heaven is watching the \Nlabyrinths of the world!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.35,0:00:28.29,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Full throttle reasoning skills \Npenetrate all mysteries!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.63,0:00:30.30,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Before tackling the Scarlet Case,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.30,0:00:32.09,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,we head to a karate dojo with Sonoko.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.64,0:00:34.51,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.51,0:00:36.51,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,with the body of a child \Nand the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.51,0:00:38.51,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.98,0:02:13.99,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(398,1)}Mystery of the Missing Black Belt
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.68,0:02:10.99,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"Mystery of the Missing Black Belt!"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.46,0:02:20.78,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm impressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.86,0:02:24.60,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Makoto-san is so cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.60,0:02:25.81,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.28,0:02:29.03,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you so indifferent?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.03,0:02:31.68,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,They're doing us a big \Nfavor by letting us watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.68,0:02:34.30,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Try to look a little happier.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.30,0:02:37.42,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one who forced me to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.98,0:02:42.39,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to go to USJ with everyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.39,0:02:44.39,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,We came all the way to Osaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.40,0:02:48.27,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You should've brought Ran-neechan \Nwith you to watch karate.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.48,0:02:51.77,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Ran has to watch the kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.19,0:02:54.37,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, if Ran came,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.37,0:02:57.68,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,she and Makoto-san would end \Nup talking about karate.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.50,0:03:01.12,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't want to come alone,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.12,0:03:04.15,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,so you were my only option.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.07,0:03:06.95,DCMain,HIROKI,0000,0000,0000,,Osu!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.95,0:03:08.33,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Osu!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.33,0:03:10.08,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for having us!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.30,0:03:12.26,DCMain,KATSUTO,0000,0000,0000,,Hiroki, your karate gi...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.26,0:03:13.31,DCMain,HIROKI,0000,0000,0000,,My old one was falling apart,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.31,0:03:15.09,DCMain,HIROKI,0000,0000,0000,,so my parents bought me a new one.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.38,0:03:18.29,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Kids' practice is starting now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.29,0:03:20.43,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Makoto-san is their guest.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.43,0:03:22.57,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Who's the old man standing over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.47,0:03:29.73,Tatsuhito,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Takami Tatsuhito (70) \NTenshin Style Karate \NEighth Master
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.53,0:03:27.69,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}He's the eighth master of Tenshin style karate,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.69,0:03:29.73,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Takami Tatsuhito-sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.73,0:03:30.78,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.78,0:03:34.12,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's his relationship with Kyogoku-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.82,0:03:38.95,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I-I think they've known \Neach other for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.74,0:03:41.61,DCMain,KYOGOKU,0000,0000,0000,,While I was in grade school,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.87,0:03:44.38,DCMain,KYOGOKU,0000,0000,0000,,I once stopped making progress \Nwith my karate training.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.92,0:03:47.53,DCMain,KYOGOKU,0000,0000,0000,,When I came to Osaka on a family trip,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.53,0:03:49.32,DCMain,KYOGOKU,0000,0000,0000,,I happened to meet Takami-sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.91,0:03:56.92,DCMain,KYOGOKU,0000,0000,0000,,I practiced with him one time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.71,0:04:02.87,DCMain,KYOGOKU,0000,0000,0000,,During that practice session, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.24,0:04:30.16,DCItalic,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Win without fighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.03,0:04:37.14,DCItalic,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Consider the meaning of these words.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.62,0:04:44.55,DCMain,KYOGOKU,0000,0000,0000,,I am who I am now because of that lesson.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.85,0:04:46.91,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Win without fighting?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.91,0:04:48.18,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.18,0:04:49.18,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Doesn't it mean
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.46,0:04:53.84,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,you shouldn't strike the first blow?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.78,0:04:59.43,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone interprets it differently.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.43,0:05:01.44,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,There's no one right answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.15,0:05:04.80,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,The children's practice is starting.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.80,0:05:06.70,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Take your time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.21,0:05:08.13,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.52,0:05:21.15,DCMain,KYOGOKU,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right, Sonoko-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.15,0:05:22.40,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.40,0:05:24.72,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I had a touch of a cold, but I'm over it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.08,0:05:28.59,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, that sparring you \Ndid earlier was so cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.51,0:05:32.10,DCMain,KYOGOKU,0000,0000,0000,,Th-Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.70,0:05:34.98,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Let's begin practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.31,0:05:36.64,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Osu!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.03,0:05:40.64,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm always surprised by \Nthe growth of children.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.81,0:05:40.64,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}One, two, three, four!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.64,0:05:43.42,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Over there is Kadota Hiroki.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.64,0:05:43.92,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Five, six, seven, eight!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.23,0:05:47.74,Hiroki,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,227)}Kadota Hiroki (10)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.42,0:05:47.23,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}His body was stiff, and he \Nhad trouble with stretches.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.92,0:05:47.23,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}One, two, three, four!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.23,0:05:49.78,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Five, six, seven, eight!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.23,0:05:49.78,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Now I hardly recognize him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.78,0:05:53.71,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,He's become somewhat of a leader recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.71,0:05:55.77,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,He's dependable.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.29,0:05:58.40,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Next to him is Kawaguchi Katsuto.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.40,0:06:00.26,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm excited for his future.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.26,0:06:02.80,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,His body is large, but he's timid.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.80,0:06:05.52,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}He had trouble displaying his \Nabilities in demonstrations.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.05,0:06:09.34,Katsuto,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,250)}Kawaguchi Katsuto (10)
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.52,0:06:09.93,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Now he's passed the shodan \Ntest and wears a black belt.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.32,0:06:11.44,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.44,0:06:13.68,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,There's also Obashi Norio.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.10,0:06:17.73,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}He was a weak runner and became \Nexhausted before the run was over,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.14,0:06:19.98,Norio,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,250)}Obashi Norio (10)
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.73,0:06:20.44,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}but now he completes them easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.99,0:06:24.75,DCMain,KYOGOKU,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that because you're a good teacher?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.75,0:06:27.97,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not so sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.57,0:06:31.15,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for coming today.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.15,0:06:35.51,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,You're a hero to the children, Kyogoku-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.51,0:06:37.45,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,This will be a good memory for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.90,0:06:44.23,DCMain,NORIO,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei, my stomach hurts.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.23,0:06:46.95,DCMain,NORIO,0000,0000,0000,,Would it be all right if \NI skipped practice today?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.95,0:06:48.72,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.18,0:06:51.14,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.14,0:06:52.72,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Do you need someone to take you home?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.20,0:06:57.00,DCMain,NORIO,0000,0000,0000,,No, I can make it by myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.42,0:07:00.64,DCMain,NORIO,0000,0000,0000,,I should get better with some rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.96,0:07:03.50,DCMain,HIROKI,0000,0000,0000,,Let's begin practicing the fundamentals!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.86,0:07:18.02,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei, what is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.04,0:07:22.64,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,It's a display of the medals and \Ntrophies I've won in various matches.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.64,0:07:24.51,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,I told them not to,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.51,0:07:26.55,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,but my students insisted.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.86,0:07:28.80,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's that on top?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.72,0:07:33.43,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,It's the belt the master of this \Ndojo has worn for generations.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.43,0:07:36.17,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,It's a symbol of the blood \Nand sweat of our seniors.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.17,0:07:37.81,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,I've been practicing hard,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.02,0:07:41.09,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,so as not to bring shame upon the belt.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.09,0:07:43.89,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's the belt you're wearing now?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.89,0:07:46.32,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,An ordinary belt you'd find anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.57,0:07:49.44,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But aren't you the master of the dojo?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.44,0:07:51.77,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you wear that belt?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.36,0:07:54.57,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.20,0:07:56.92,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,I should be getting back to practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.68,0:07:59.41,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,What's gotten into him?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.41,0:08:02.64,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Since Takami-sensei became the master,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.64,0:08:05.83,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,a lot of people quit over \Nhis intense practices.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.16,0:08:09.99,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,On top of that, he doesn't charge \Nthe children for practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.99,0:08:11.03,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.03,0:08:12.34,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,You mean it's free?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.86,0:08:14.72,DCMain,ASAI,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go running!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.72,0:08:16.30,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Osu!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.75,0:08:19.85,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Kyogoku-kun, we need to talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.35,0:08:21.09,DCMain,KYOGOKU,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.49,0:08:24.10,DCMain,KAJIYOSHI,0000,0000,0000,,Takami-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.14,0:08:27.11,Ginji,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,1)}Kajiyoshi Ginji (42)
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.68,0:08:26.28,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Kajiyoshi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.50,0:08:31.11,DCMain,KAJIYOSHI,0000,0000,0000,,Could I get your signature today?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.44,0:08:32.99,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.99,0:08:35.69,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Could you wait a little longer?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.69,0:08:37.59,DCMain,KAJIYOSHI,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.59,0:08:41.93,DCMain,KAJIYOSHI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm here because you said you wanted \Nto sell this place as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.93,0:08:45.49,DCMain,KAJIYOSHI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm prepared to buy it \Nfor a reasonable amount.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.49,0:08:47.84,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,I have guests right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.03,0:08:50.21,DCMain,KAJIYOSHI,0000,0000,0000,,Whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.21,0:08:51.84,DCMain,KAJIYOSHI,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be back.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.84,0:08:53.79,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Who are those guys?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.79,0:08:55.94,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I think they're black market loan sharks.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.94,0:08:57.01,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.01,0:08:58.95,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,If he can't pay,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.95,0:09:01.85,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,they're going to take this place instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.48,0:09:05.96,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They could make a lot of \Nmoney selling the land.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.23,0:09:10.98,DCMain,KYOGOKU,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei, are you serious \Nabout selling this place?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.38,0:09:13.25,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm getting old.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.25,0:09:17.24,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,It's time for me to give up \Nmy black belt and retire.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.50,0:09:18.73,DCMain,KYOGOKU,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.09,0:09:21.49,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.49,0:09:26.03,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,there's still no one worthy \Nto take over the Tenshin dojo.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.52,0:09:30.75,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I thought to \Nclose it down instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.75,0:09:33.92,DCMain,KYOGOKU,0000,0000,0000,,But as far as I can tell, you're still...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.18,0:09:37.93,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have the strength I once had.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.93,0:09:41.08,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,The strength to wear that black belt.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.53,0:09:45.68,DCMain,KYOGOKU,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.60,0:09:50.57,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Takami-sensei, what's going to happen
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.57,0:09:52.98,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,to those kids once this place is gone?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.46,0:09:57.36,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm planning to ask another \Ndojo to take them in.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.36,0:10:01.46,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't they come here because \Nthey looked up to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.46,0:10:03.37,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,You're being irresponsible!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.64,0:10:14.42,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Kyogoku-kun, what did you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.31,0:10:19.18,DCMain,ASAI,0000,0000,0000,,Th-The belt is gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.43,0:10:23.41,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Kyogoku-kun, did you...?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.41,0:10:25.43,DCMain,KYOGOKU,0000,0000,0000,,If it were me...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.93,0:10:28.33,DCMain,KYOGOKU,0000,0000,0000,,What would you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.91,0:10:36.05,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Makoto-san, is it true?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.05,0:10:38.56,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Explain yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.96,0:10:42.74,DCMain,KYOGOKU,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like you to reconsider closing the dojo.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.74,0:10:43.37,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.16,0:10:47.54,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.54,0:10:49.12,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,The decision's already been made.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.51,0:10:52.50,DCMain,KYOGOKU,0000,0000,0000,,Then I challenge you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.39,0:10:56.16,DCMain,KYOGOKU,0000,0000,0000,,If I win, keep the dojo open.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.16,0:10:57.83,DCMain,KYOGOKU,0000,0000,0000,,If you win,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.83,0:11:00.13,DCMain,KYOGOKU,0000,0000,0000,,I'll return the belt.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.32,0:11:04.14,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure we can't reach a compromise?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.51,0:11:05.20,DCMain,KYOGOKU,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.65,0:11:09.64,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.23,0:11:11.18,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,I accept.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.18,0:11:12.15,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.15,0:11:14.90,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Makoto-san, don't do this!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.90,0:11:16.23,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.22,0:11:42.32,DCMain,KATSUTO,0000,0000,0000,,What are we going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.32,0:11:43.86,DCMain,KATSUTO,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe this is happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.86,0:11:44.74,DCMain,HITOKI,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.68,0:11:47.91,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Makoto-san, stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.91,0:11:50.06,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,You're scaring the children!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.31,0:11:51.60,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Makoto-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.32,0:12:01.86,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.64,0:12:04.11,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, crap.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.62,0:12:05.88,DCMain,KYOGOKU,0000,0000,0000,,Sonoko-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.88,0:12:08.27,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Makoto-san didn't do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.37,0:12:11.66,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,He's just protecting the person who did.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.11,0:12:13.16,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.16,0:12:15.54,DCMain,MATSUMOTO,0000,0000,0000,,Who has the keys to the display room?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.05,0:12:17.25,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Only me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.25,0:12:20.15,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,There's another exit.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.15,0:12:21.70,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,The window in the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.70,0:12:25.09,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Not even a child could \Nfit through that window.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.39,0:12:27.03,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,There's a drainpipe.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.03,0:12:30.35,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,You could use it to climb up to the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.66,0:12:33.38,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,The drainpipe is falling apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.78,0:12:35.38,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,It's useless.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.38,0:12:39.36,DCMain,ASAI,0000,0000,0000,,Only Kyogoku-kun could've stolen the belt.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.36,0:12:42.11,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,If you're so sure, why don't you search him?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.93,0:12:48.18,DCMain,ASAI,0000,0000,0000,,He doesn't have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.18,0:12:50.32,DCMain,MATSUMOTO,0000,0000,0000,,He could've hidden it somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.32,0:12:54.12,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Surprised by the sound of \NMakoto-san breaking the lock,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.12,0:12:56.04,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,we ran to the dojo.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.04,0:12:59.52,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,There was no time for \NMakoto-san to hide the belt.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.52,0:13:00.63,DCMain,ASAI,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.89,0:13:02.79,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,She's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.29,0:13:06.31,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know where the belt is?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.31,0:13:07.26,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.12,0:13:09.35,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Where is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.74,0:13:13.24,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Kadota Hiroki-kun, Kawaguchi Katsuto-kun,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.24,0:13:16.75,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,and the absent Obashi Norio-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.49,0:13:19.86,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,They know where it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.86,0:13:21.48,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.07,0:13:25.86,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,You've been planning to \Nsteal Takami-sensei's belt
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.14,0:13:30.12,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,for a while now, haven't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.54,0:13:33.54,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Is this true?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.24,0:13:35.28,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.28,0:13:37.17,DCMain,ASAI,0000,0000,0000,,That's odd, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.37,0:13:40.60,DCMain,ASAI,0000,0000,0000,,I was out running with the children.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.60,0:13:43.63,DCMain,ASAI,0000,0000,0000,,They were with us the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.35,0:13:47.08,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Do you always run along the same course?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.08,0:13:47.91,DCMain,ASAI,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.91,0:13:50.89,DCMain,ASAI,0000,0000,0000,,There's a park about five minutes from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.33,0:13:56.06,DCMain,ASAI,0000,0000,0000,,We do a head count there before \Nrunning along the river.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.06,0:13:59.51,DCMain,ASAI,0000,0000,0000,,We cross the third bridge and run \Nback along the opposite side,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.51,0:14:01.82,DCMain,ASAI,0000,0000,0000,,do another head count at the park,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.05,0:14:03.61,DCMain,ASAI,0000,0000,0000,,and come back here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.06,0:14:05.89,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,How do you explain that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.89,0:14:07.81,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,You say they were all there,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.81,0:14:11.49,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,but you didn't check each \Nof their faces, did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.81,0:14:12.99,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.99,0:14:15.75,DCMain,ASAI,0000,0000,0000,,N-No, I didn't check their faces.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.01,0:14:19.92,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,They swapped places when you \Nfirst did a head count at the park.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.46,0:14:24.00,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Hiroki-kun and Obashi Norio-kun, \Nwho had gone home earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.43,0:14:29.01,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Norio-kun pretended to be \NHiroki-kun and ran with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.24,0:14:30.45,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.45,0:14:33.39,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,After leaving the park alone,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.39,0:14:35.39,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Hiroki-kun returned to the dojo.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.39,0:14:38.90,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,He snuck around the back \Nto avoid being spotted,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.90,0:14:40.17,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,climbed the wall,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.17,0:14:43.40,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,took the belt from the display \Ncase through the window,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.67,0:14:45.15,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,and left.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.15,0:14:46.38,DCMain,MATSUMOTO,0000,0000,0000,,That's ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.38,0:14:50.47,DCMain,MATSUMOTO,0000,0000,0000,,It's impossible for a child to \Nclimb that wall without a rope.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.47,0:14:53.71,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,It's possible using the drainpipe.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.37,0:14:56.66,DCMain,MATSUMOTO,0000,0000,0000,,But the drainpipe's falling apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.03,0:14:59.41,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,What if it were a small, flexible child?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.80,0:15:03.16,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Hiroki, is this true?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.16,0:15:04.54,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Did you take the belt?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.30,0:15:12.12,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,He could just barely reach the belt
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.12,0:15:14.89,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,by putting his body through the \Nwindow and stretching his arms.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.15,0:15:20.62,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,But his collar got caught \Non the edge of the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.21,0:15:25.61,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,The frayed collar on \NHiroki-kun's new karate gi
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.94,0:15:27.34,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,proves it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.95,0:15:30.90,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Hiroki-kun took the belt to the park,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.34,0:15:34.25,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,and waited for the others \Nto return from their run.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.32,0:15:37.46,DCMain,ASAI,0000,0000,0000,,But where's the belt?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.46,0:15:39.43,DCMain,MATSUMOTO,0000,0000,0000,,There's nowhere to hide it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.43,0:15:41.00,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Kawaguchi Katsuto-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.99,0:15:44.39,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Could you take off your belt?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.12,0:15:52.51,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Th-This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.73,0:15:57.70,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,They didn't just switch people \Nat the park after the run.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.31,0:16:00.52,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,They also switched belts.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.00,0:16:04.01,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Katsuto-kun was able to wear a black belt
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.01,0:16:05.71,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,because he just passed his shodan test.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.02,0:16:08.02,DCMain,HIROKI,0000,0000,0000,,Norio!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.03,0:16:11.07,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.64,0:16:13.42,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Why would you do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.47,0:16:17.99,DCMain,HIROKI,0000,0000,0000,,We wanted you to keep the dojo open.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.31,0:16:23.62,DCMain,HIROKI,0000,0000,0000,,We heard you talking on the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.62,0:16:25.88,DCMain,HIROKI,0000,0000,0000,,You said you were going to close the dojo
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.88,0:16:27.25,DCMain,HIROKI,0000,0000,0000,,because you lost your passion for karate.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.29,0:16:31.75,DCMain,HIROKI,0000,0000,0000,,We wanted to keep practicing here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.75,0:16:35.27,DCMain,HIROKI,0000,0000,0000,,We wanted you to teach us more.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.83,0:16:40.86,DCMain,KATSUTO,0000,0000,0000,,You said now that you \Nhad the belt you wanted,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.86,0:16:43.00,DCMain,KATSUTO,0000,0000,0000,,you had no regrets.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.00,0:16:45.35,DCMain,NORIO,0000,0000,0000,,We thought you'd want to keep training
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.35,0:16:48.02,DCMain,NORIO,0000,0000,0000,,if the belt disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.44,0:16:50.34,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,B-Boys...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.92,0:16:52.94,DCMain,CHILD A,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't quit!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.24,0:16:56.38,DCMain,CHILD B,0000,0000,0000,,Please keep the dojo open!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.38,0:16:57.91,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.32,0:17:06.17,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Makoto-san, you understood \Nhow the children felt.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.48,0:17:08.28,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,That's why you knew immediately
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.28,0:17:11.94,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,who did it when you noticed \Nthe belt was missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.05,0:17:17.55,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,The boys put their plan into motion
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.55,0:17:20.05,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,because they didn't want you to quit.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.83,0:17:22.68,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,It took them a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.91,0:17:24.81,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,A long time?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.77,0:17:27.44,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.04,0:17:30.69,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,In order to climb the wall to the window,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.69,0:17:34.64,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Hiroki-kun had to make \Nhis stiff body flexible.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.31,0:17:39.12,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Only the small Hiroki-kun could \Nclimb the deteriorated drainpipe,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.12,0:17:42.46,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,and fit through the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.73,0:17:47.88,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Katsuto-kun worked hard to pass his shodan \Ntest so he could wear a black belt.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.41,0:17:50.48,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Only the large Katsuto-kun
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.48,0:17:53.55,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,could wear an adult-sized belt.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.36,0:17:58.88,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,And Norio-kun worked to \Nget better at running.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.88,0:18:00.77,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,He had to keep up with the others,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.77,0:18:04.43,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,while pretending to be Hiroki-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.41,0:18:10.50,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Boys...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.12,0:18:15.69,DCMain,KAJIYOSHI,0000,0000,0000,,You guys having a meeting?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.91,0:18:19.67,DCMain,KAJIYOSHI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm here to collect your \Nsignature, just like we agreed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.34,0:18:22.78,DCMain,KYOGOKU,0000,0000,0000,,Take off your shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.78,0:18:23.70,DCMain,KAJIYOSHI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.20,0:18:26.18,DCMain,KYOGOKU,0000,0000,0000,,This is a dojo.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.76,0:18:28.58,DCMain,KYOGOKU,0000,0000,0000,,You can't wear your shoes in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.87,0:18:30.58,DCMain,KAJIYOSHI,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.58,0:18:33.50,DCMain,KAJIYOSHI,0000,0000,0000,,Mind your own business.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.24,0:18:36.70,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Kajiyoshi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.30,0:18:39.64,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.64,0:18:42.89,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,but could we forget \Nabout what we discussed?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.15,0:18:47.19,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,It seems I was wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.19,0:18:50.15,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I'd already done everything,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.66,0:18:53.39,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,but I still have a lot to learn.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.39,0:18:55.44,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,I need training.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.07,0:18:59.36,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,These children taught me that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.36,0:19:01.07,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,These children—
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.28,0:19:04.70,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,and I—
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.70,0:19:07.00,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,still need this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.75,0:19:10.24,DCMain,ALL,0000,0000,0000,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.24,0:19:11.50,DCMain,KAJIYOSHI,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.91,0:19:16.86,DCMain,KAJIYOSHI,0000,0000,0000,,You expect me to just accept that now?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.04,0:19:20.85,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}What's going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.04,0:19:21.94,DCMain,KAJIYOSHI,0000,0000,0000,,Either return all the \Nmoney you owe immediately,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.94,0:19:24.65,DCMain,KAJIYOSHI,0000,0000,0000,,or vacate this property.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.65,0:19:26.36,DCMain,KAJIYOSHI,0000,0000,0000,,It's one or the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.82,0:19:42.82,DCMain,KAJIYOSHI,0000,0000,0000,,What, you wanna fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.82,0:19:43.91,DCMain,KAJIYOSHI,0000,0000,0000,,Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.91,0:19:44.87,DCMain,KAJIYOSHI,0000,0000,0000,,Get him!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.84,0:19:53.63,DCMain,KAJIYOSHI,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get ahead of yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.63,0:20:05.89,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you leave for today?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.90,0:20:12.10,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Win without fighting.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.88,0:20:15.69,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm still a long way away from that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.94,0:20:19.98,DCMain,TAKAMI,0000,0000,0000,,Now let's begin practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.40,0:21:46.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad a lawyer agreed \Nto help Takami-sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.00,0:21:49.26,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I had someone look into Kajiyoshi's company,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.26,0:21:50.11,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,and it was totally shady.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.11,0:21:51.83,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,It was a corrupt moneylender.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.83,0:21:53.82,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Since the police will be \Ninvestigating them soon,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.82,0:21:56.62,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt he'll have to pay back his loan.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.50,0:22:00.24,DCMain,KYOGOKU,0000,0000,0000,,Sonoko-san, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.70,0:22:03.27,DCMain,KYOGOKU,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to you, the dojo will stay open.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.27,0:22:05.12,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.12,0:22:07.84,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Makoto-san, you were as cool as ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.84,0:22:10.37,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so glad I came to watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.63,0:22:12.97,DCMain,KYOGOKU,0000,0000,0000,,Sonoko-san, are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.92,0:22:16.06,DCMain,KYOGOKU,0000,0000,0000,,You have a bit of a fever.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.84,0:22:17.93,DCMain,KYOGOKU,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.93,0:22:19.85,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.15,0:22:22.40,DCMain,KYOGOKU,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe your cold is coming back.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.40,0:22:23.18,DCMain,KYOGOKU,0000,0000,0000,,Take this.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.18,0:22:27.00,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, Makoto-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.29,0:22:32.49,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.49,0:22:34.74,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Sonoko, your face is red.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.74,0:22:36.04,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.58,0:22:38.22,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.22,0:22:41.84,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Makoto-san and I are going to have some fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.84,0:22:42.95,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.72,0:22:49.13,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You can't be serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.82,0:22:50.89,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,Come with us, miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.89,0:22:53.45,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-Wh-What is this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.45,0:22:55.40,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Did you do this, Makoto-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.40,0:22:56.54,DCMain,KYOGOKU,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.54,0:22:58.29,DCMain,KYOGOKU,0000,0000,0000,,I called them.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.29,0:23:00.90,DCMain,KYOGOKU,0000,0000,0000,,You shouldn't underestimate a cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.40,0:23:03.47,DCMain,KYOGOKU,0000,0000,0000,,Colds lead to all kinds of illnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.47,0:23:06.38,DCMain,KYOGOKU,0000,0000,0000,,You need rest to get better.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.53,0:23:10.13,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Let go of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.13,0:23:14.03,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to USJ with Makoto-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.63,0:23:19.79,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They're gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.79,0:23:21.60,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Let me out!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.60,0:23:26.66,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to USJ!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.08,0:23:32.43,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Sonoko would thank Kyogoku-san later.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.87,0:23:34.78,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Later we got caught up
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.78,0:23:38.18,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,in a major case involving
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.18,0:23:40.65,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,a TV station.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.94,0:24:08.96,DCEpPreview,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.84,0:23:49.57,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That came from downstairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.80,0:23:54.05,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.54,0:23:56.59,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,There's blood on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.59,0:23:59.20,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,I think we can assume it was \Nused to commit the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.82,0:24:02.58,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Chiba, where did you find this?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.16,0:24:05.96,DCMain,CHIBA,0000,0000,0000,,In this apartment's dump site.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.36,0:24:07.28,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.96,0:24:14.97,DCNextEp,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,The Socialite Couple's Secret
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.71,0:24:13.46,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode of Conan is \N"The Socialite Couple's Secret!"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.98,0:24:34.99,Hint,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Closet
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.64,0:24:33.06,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.06,0:24:34.99,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A closet!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.99,0:24:36.40,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Let me out!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.99,0:24:39.99,Don'tMiss,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Don't miss the next episode.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.40,0:24:37.97,DCMain,KYOGOKU,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Do you not like being with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.97,0:24:39.69,DCMain,SONOKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}What? No, I don't mind.
